<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p>The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BritishFilmInstitute" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BritishFilmInstitute">British Film Institute</a> surveyed a thousand members of the British public over what was their favourite British movie from the 20th century. These films were selected over how "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PatrioticFervor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PatrioticFervor">culturally British</a>" they were, from the cast and crew to the national pride.
</p><p>Director <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DavidLean" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DavidLean">David Lean</a> had the most films appear in the list, whereas actors Sir <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MichaelCaine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MichaelCaine">Michael Caine</a>, Sir <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AlecGuinness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AlecGuinness">Alec Guinness</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JulieChristie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JulieChristie">Julie Christie</a> had the most film appearances in the list.
</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><hr><h2>The list</h2>
